casebody.data:
DUNBAR HOMES, INC., Plaintiff,
v.
The ZONING BOARD OF ADJUSTMENT OF the TOWNSHIP OF FRANKLIN, Defendant-Respondent,
and
Township of Franklin, Defendant-Respondent. M-1314 September Term 2016
079076 Supreme Court of New Jersey. July 20, 2017

ORDER

It is ORDERED that the motion of the New Jersey Builders Association, NAIOP New Jersey Chapter, Inc., and International Council of Shopping Centers for leave to file a brief and argue as amicus curiae is granted. The parties may serve and file briefs in response on or before August 21, 2017. Oral argument is limited to five minutes.
